<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Thinktool &ndash; Log In</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/landing.css">
    <link rel="icon" href="/icon.png" type="image/png">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <script>
      fetch("{{apiUrl}}/username", {"credentials": "include"}).then((response) => {
        if (response.status === 200) {
          console.log("Already logged in. Redirecting to app page.");
          window.location = "/app.html";
        }
      })
    </script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header id="top-bar">
      <span id="logo">Thinktool</span>
    </header>
    <main class="login">
      <div>
        <h1>Sign up or log in.</h1>
        <form action="{{apiUrl}}/" method="POST">
          <div class="form-table">
            <div class="entry">
              <label>Username</label>
              <input name="user" required/>
            </div>
            <div class="entry">
              <label for="password">Password</label>
              <input id="password" type="password" name="password" required/>
            </div>
          </div>
          <input type="submit" name="login" value="Log in"/>
          <input type="submit" name="signup" value="Sign up"/>
        </form>
      </div>

      <aside class="disclaimer">
        <h1>Thank you for trying Thinktool!</h1>
        <p>
          I'm passionate making software that helps people be smarter; that's
          why I'm making Thinktool.  However, I'm also one person doing this in
          my spare time.
          <strong>Expect unstable, preview-quality software that is filled with
          bugs and missing critical features.</strong>
        </p>
        <p>
          If you do decide to check it out, I would <em>love</em> hear your
          opinions! Send me an email with your feedback to
          <a class="email" href="mailto:jonas@thinktool.io"><span>jonas@thinktool.io</span></a>.
          Also feel free to message me if you need help with anything.
        </p>
      </aside>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
